MapStruct doesn&#39;t directly support mapping elements of an array by their index in the way you&#39;re attempting to do it. Instead, you can create a custom method in your mapper interface to manually perform this mapping.

    @Mapper
    public interface MyMapper {
        MyMapper INSTANCE = Mappers.getMapper(MyMapper.class);
    
        @Mapping(target = &quot;person&quot;, source = &quot;people&quot;)
        Destination mapToDestination(Source source);
    
        default Person mapPersonFromArray(Person[] people) {
            return (people != null &amp;&amp; people.length &gt; 0) ? people[0] : null;
        }
    }

In this example:

@Mapping(target = &quot;person&quot;, source = &quot;people&quot;): This tells MapStruct to use the mapPersonFromArray method to map the people field to the person field.

default Person mapPersonFromArray(Person[] people): This is a custom method that manually performs the mapping. It checks if the array is not null and has at least one element, and if so, it returns the first element; otherwise, it returns null.

Remember to adjust the Person class and the mapper interface according to your actual classes and requirements.

This way, MapStruct will use the custom method to map the first element of the people array to the person field in the Destination class.

