There is a beautiful way to work with Spring.

1. Add a method `param` in BasicProcess.
```java
public interface BasicProcess {
    Message createProcess();

    String param();
}
```

2. Define your implements with @Component.
```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class WorkProcess implements BasicProcess {

    // Spring will inject bean into this field
    private final HelperService;

    @Override
    public Message createProcess() {
        //do some logic
    }

    @Override
    public String param() {
        return &quot;Work&quot;;
    }
}

@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class EatProcess implements BasicProcess {

    private FoodService;

    @Override
    public Message createProcess() {
        //do some other logic
    }

    @Override
    public String param() {
        return &quot;Food&quot;;
    }
}
```
3. Inject all BasicProcess into your factory.
```Java
@Service
public class Factory implements InitializingBean {

    // Spring will inject all bean which implements BasicProcess into this field.
    @Autowired
    private List&lt;BasicProcess&gt; basicProcessList;

    private final Map&lt;String, BasicProcess&gt; basicProcessMap = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();

    @Override
    public void afterPropertiesSet() {
        if (Objects.nonNull(basicProcessList)) {
            basicProcessList.forEach(
                    process -&gt; basicProcessMap.put(process.param(), process)
            );
            basicProcessList = null; // help gc
        }
    }

    public BasicProcess factoryMethod(String param) {
        return basicProcessMap.get(param);
    }
}
```

